1. Danas ćemo raspravljati o *temi* klimatskih promena. (*temi* - topic, subject) Today we will discuss the *topic* of climate change.

2. Učiteljica je zadala novu *temu* za pismeni zadatak. (nova *tema* - new topic, subject) The teacher assigned a new *topic* for the written assignment.

3. U knjizi je obrađena *tema* ljubavi na jedan vrlo originalan način. (obrađena *tema* - discussed topic, subject) The book covered the *topic* of love in a very original way.

4. On ne voli da se bavi *temama* o kojima ne zna dovoljno. (*temama* - topics, subjects) He doesn't like to deal with *topics* he doesn't know enough about.

5. Novinar je intervjuisao glumicu o njenim novim *temama*. (njenim novim *temama* - her new topics, subjects) The journalist interviewed the actress about her new *topics*.

6. Na sastanku smo predložili nekoliko *tema* koje bismo mogli razmatrati. (nekoliko *tema* - several topics, subjects) During the meeting, we proposed several *topics* that we could discuss.

7. Napisao je dugi esej o *temi* modernog društva. (*temi* - topic, subject) He wrote a long essay on the *topic* of modern society.

8. Završio je školu za novinare i sada se specijalizuje za sportske *teme*. (sportske *teme* - sports topics, subjects) He finished journalism school and now specializes in sports *topics*.

9. Njegova poslednja knjiga je pokrenula mnoge *teme* u književnim krugovima. (mnoge *teme* - many topics, subjects) His latest book has sparked many *topics* in literary circles.

10. Uvek se trudim da pronađem *temu* koja će me inspirisati da pišem. (*temu* - topic, subject) I always try to find a *topic* that will inspire me to write.